text: Sir Harry Innes, 4th Baronet (c. 1670–1721) was a Scottish politician and baronet. He represented the Parliament of Scotland constituency of Elginshire 1704–1707.Complete Baronetage, vol. II, p. 281. He was a member of the Innes baronets. ==References== Category:1670 births Category:1721 deaths Category:Baronets in the Baronetage of the United Kingdom Category:Shire Commissioners to the Parliament of Scotland Category:Politics of Moray
